<h1>Fit</h1>

{{#embed "patterns.organisms.block.block" block_classes="" body_classes=""  }}
  {{#content "content"}}
    <h2>default</h2>
    <p>Both the body and media will be inside the block container with padding between them and the edges.</p>
  {{/content}}
{{/embed}}

{{#embed "patterns.organisms.block.block" body_classes="" media_classes="fit-flush-top" }}
  {{#content "content"}}
    <h3 class="mzp-c-billboard-title">fit-flush-top</h3>
    <p class="mzp-c-billboard-desc">Chaning the fit to "flush" will make the media flush to the block container. It can be set on all sides with <code>fit-flush</code> or on individual sides with <code>fit-flush-top</code>, <code>fit-flush-bottom</code>, or <code>fit-flush-side</code>. The image can only be flush to the outside of the container, not to the text container.</p>
  {{/content}}
{{/embed}}

{{#embed "patterns.organisms.block.block" body_classes="" media_classes="fit-flush" }}
  {{#content "content"}}
    <h3 class="mzp-c-billboard-title">fit-flush</h3>
  {{/content}}
{{/embed}}

{{#embed "patterns.organisms.block.block" body_classes="" media_classes="fit-pop-top" }}
  {{#content "content"}}
    <h3 class="mzp-c-billboard-title">fit-pop-top</h3>
    <p class="mzp-c-billboard-desc">Chaning the fit to "pop" will make the media pop out of the block container. It can be set on all sides with <code>fit-pop</code> or on individual sides with <code>fit-pop-top</code>, <code>fit-pop-bottom</code>, or <code>fit-pop-side</code>. The image can only pop out of the container on the top, bottom, and side away from the body text.</p>
  {{/content}}
{{/embed}}

{{#embed "patterns.organisms.block.block" body_classes="" media_classes="fit-pop" }}
  {{#content "content"}}
    <h4 class="mzp-c-billboard-title">fit-pop</h4>
  {{/content}}
{{/embed}}

{{#embed "patterns.organisms.block.block" body_classes="" media_classes="fit-flush-bottom fit-pop-top constrain-width" }}
  {{#content "content"}}
    <h3 class="mzp-c-billboard-title">Mixed flush and pop</h3>
    <p>You can mix fit-flush and fit-pop classes, here is fit-flush-bottom fit-pop-top.</p>
  {{/content}}
{{/embed}}

{{#embed "patterns.organisms.block.block" body_classes="" media_classes="fit-flush constrain-width" }}
  {{#content "content"}}
    <h3 class="mzp-c-billboard-title">fit with constraint</h3>
    <p>In the examples above the image overflows the container. If you want it to stay inside the container one of the contstraint classes will need to be added.</p>
  {{/content}}
{{/embed}}

